--;\\n            }\\n            else if(Character.isLetter(ans.charAt(start)) && !Character.isLetter(ans.charAt(end)))\\n            {\\n                start++;\\n            }\\n            else\\n            {\\n                start++;\\n                end--;\\n            }\\n           \\n        }\\n\\n        return ans.toString();\\n\\n\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"reverse-letters-then-special-characters-in-a-string","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":821},{"id":1903077971,"question_id":1,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1\xc2\xa0month, 3\xc2\xa0weeks","timestamp":1769869738,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1903077971/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum","memory":"47.5 MB","code":"class Solution {\\n    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {\\n        int ans[] = new int[2];\\n        HashMap<Integer,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\\n        for(int i = 0 ; i < nums.length ; i++)\\n        {\\n            int secondVal = target-nums[i];\\n            if(map.containsKey(secondVal))\\n            {\\n                ans[0] = i;\\n                ans[1] = map.get(secondVal);\\n                return ans;\\n            }\\n            map.put(nums[i],i);\\n\\n        }\\n        return ans;\\n\\n        \\n        \\n    }\\n\\n   \\n}","compare_result":"111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"two-sum","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":820},{"id":1901981505,"question_id":101,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1\xc2\xa0month, 3\xc2\xa0weeks","timestamp":1769777290,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"0 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1901981505/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Symmetric Tree","memory":"43.7 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\\n * public class TreeNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     TreeNode left;\\n *     TreeNode right;\\n *     TreeNode() {}\\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\\n *         this.val = val;\\n *         this.left = left;\\n *         this.right = right;\\n *     }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public boolean isSymmetric(TreeNode root) {\\n        if(root == null)\\n        {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n        return dfs(root.left,root.right);\\n    }\\n    public static boolean dfs(TreeNode root1 , TreeNode root2)\\n    {\\n        if((root1 == null && root2 != null) || root1 != null && root2 ==null)\\n        {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        else if(root1 == null && root2 == null)\\n        {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n        else if(root1.val != root2.val)\\n        {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        \\n        return dfs(root1.left,root2.right) && dfs(root1.right,root2.left);\\n\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"11111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"symmetric-tree","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":819},{"id":1901970206,"question_id":404,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1\xc2\xa0month, 3\xc2\xa0weeks","timestamp":1769776295,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"0 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1901970206/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Sum of Left Leaves","memory":"43.2 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\\n * public class TreeNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     TreeNode left;\\n *     TreeNode right;\\n *     TreeNode() {}\\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\\n *         this.val = val;\\n *         this.left = left;\\n *         this.right = right;\\n *     }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public int sumOfLeftLeaves(TreeNode root) {\\n        int sum[] = new int[1];\\n        dfs(root,sum,false);\\n        return sum[0];\\n    }\\n    public static void dfs(TreeNode root , int[] sum, boolean isleft)\\n    {\\n        if(root == null)\\n        {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        if(isleaf(root) && isleft)\\n        {\\n            sum[0] += root.val;\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        dfs(root.left,sum,true);\\n        dfs(root.right,sum,false);\\n    }\\n\\n    public static boolean isleaf(TreeNode root)\\n    {\\n        if(root.left == null && root.right == null)\\n        {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n        return false;\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"1111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"sum-of-left-leaves","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":818},{"id":1901969442,"question_id":404,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1\xc2\xa0month, 3\xc2\xa0weeks","timestamp":1769776224,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"0 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1901969442/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Sum of Left Leaves","memory":"43.1 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\\n * public class TreeNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     TreeNode left;\\n *     TreeNode right;\\n *     TreeNode() {}\\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\\n *         this.val = val;\\n *         this.left = left;\\n *         this.right = right;\\n *     }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public int sumOfLeftLeaves(TreeNode root) {\\n        int sum[] = new int[1];\\n        dfs(root,sum,false);\\n        return sum[0];\\n    }\\n    public static void dfs(TreeNode root , int[] sum, boolean isleft)\\n    {\\n        if(root == null)\\n        {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        if(isleaf(root) && isleft)\\n        {\\n            sum[0] += root.val;\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        dfs(root.left,sum,true);\\n        dfs(root.right,sum,false);\\n    }\\n\\n    public static boolean isleaf(TreeNode root)\\n    {\\n        if(root.left == null && root.right == null)\\n        {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n        return false;\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"1111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"sum-of-left-leaves","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":817},{"id":1901891878,"question_id":513,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1\xc2\xa0month, 3\xc2\xa0weeks","timestamp":1769769277,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"3 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1901891878/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find Bottom Left Tree Value","memory":"46.3 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\\n * public class TreeNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     TreeNode left;\\n *     TreeNode right;\\n *     TreeNode() {}\\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\\n *         this.val = val;\\n *         this.left = left;\\n *         this.right = right;\\n *     }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public int findBottomLeftValue(TreeNode root) {\\n        Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<>();\\n        int leftmost = 0;\\n        queue.offer(root);\\n        while(!queue.isEmpty())\\n        {\\n            int levelsize = queue.size();\\n            boolean found = false;\\n            for(int i = 0 ; i < levelsize ; i++)\\n            {\\n                TreeNode node = queue.poll();\\n                if(!found)\\n                {\\n                    leftmost = node.val;\\n                    found = true;\\n                }\\n                if(node.left != null)\\n                {\\n                    queue.offer(node.left);\\n                }\\n                if(node.right != null)\\n                {\\n                    queue.offer(node.right);\\n                }\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return leftmost;\\n\\n    }\\n\\n}","compare_result":"1111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111","title_slug":"find-bottom-left-tree-value","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1,"frontend_id":816},{"id":1901876447,"question_id":515,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1\xc2\xa0month, 3\xc2\xa0weeks","timestamp":1769768089,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1901876447/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find Largest Value in Each Tree Row","memory":"47.8 MB","code":"/**\\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\\n * public class TreeNode {\\n *     int val;\\n *     TreeNode left;\\n *     TreeNode right;\\n *     TreeNode() {}\\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\\n *         this.val = val;\\n *         this.left = left;\\n *         this.right = right;\\n *     }\\n * }\\n */\\nclass Solution {\\n    public List<Integer> largestValues(TreeNode root) {\\n        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();\\n        if(root == null)\\n        {\\n            return list;\\n        }\\n        Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<>();\\n        queue.offer(root);\\n        while(!queue.isEmpty())\\n        {\\n            int levelsize = queue.size();\\n            int largest = Integer.MIN_VALUE;\\n            for(int i = 0 ; i < levelsize ; i++)\\n            {\\n                TreeNode node = queue.poll();\\n                largest = Math.max(largest,node.val);\\n                if(node.left != null)\\n                {\\n                    queue.offer(node.left);\\n                }\\n                if(node.right != null)\\n                {\\n                    queue.offer(node.right);\\n                }\\n\\n            }\\n            list.add(largest);\\n        }\\n\\n        return list;\\n    }\\n}","compare_result":"11111111111111111111111111111